Approach 2: Binary Search on Answer (Optimal)
Intuition

Possible eating speeds are sorted.

1 2 3 4 5 6 ... maxPile

If Koko can finish at speed k,

she can also finish at

k+1, k+2, k+3...

Hence the search space is monotonic.

Use Binary Search to find the smallest valid speed.

Algorithm
Search from 1 to maxPile.
Calculate hours needed at mid.
If hours ≤ h
Store answer.
Try a smaller speed.
Else
Increase speed.

Java
class Solution {

    public int minEatingSpeed(int[] piles, int h) {

        int low = 1;
        int high = 0;

        for (int pile : piles)
            high = Math.max(high, pile);

        int ans = high;

        while (low <= high) {

            int mid = low + (high - low) / 2;

            int hours = 0;

            for (int pile : piles) {
                hours += (pile + mid - 1) / mid;
            }

            if (hours <= h) {

                ans = mid;
                high = mid - 1;

            } else {

                low = mid + 1;
            }
        }

        return ans;
    }
}
