Why Use Ceiling Division?

Suppose

Pile = 7

Speed = 3

Actual hours

3 + 3 + 1

=

3 hours

Normal division

7/3 = 2

Wrong.

Use

(pile + speed - 1) / speed

Example

(7+3-1)/3

=

9/3

=

3

Equivalent to

Math.ceil((double)pile / speed)

but faster.

